1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:08,000
 [Music]

2
00:00:08,000 --> 00:00:15,000
 AI, two letters that has changed everything in just a few years.

3
00:00:15,000 --> 00:00:20,000
 Some see it as the savior for humanity.

4
00:00:20,000 --> 00:00:27,000
 Other fear that it is the terminator that will lead us to extinction.

5
00:00:27,000 --> 00:00:35,000
 Or is it just a neutral tool that we use when we see fit?

6
00:00:35,000 --> 00:00:39,000
 Is it a competitor because we are losing jobs?

7
00:00:39,000 --> 00:00:46,000
 Or is it a partner, a co-intelligence we must learn to live with?

8
00:00:46,000 --> 00:00:48,000
 Tonight we will look deeper.

9
00:00:48,000 --> 00:00:53,000
 We ask, how now shall we live as a Christian?

10
00:00:53,000 --> 00:00:59,000
 And where can we find God's wisdom in this digital age?

11
00:00:59,000 --> 00:01:04,000
 Brothers and sisters, on behalf of CJST, we welcome you to our public lecture

12
00:01:04,000 --> 00:01:08,000
 organized by the Center for Faith and Public Value.

13
00:01:08,000 --> 00:01:10,000
 I'm Alex Yeung.

14
00:01:10,000 --> 00:01:13,000
 It is very wonderful to have you all with us here.

15
00:01:13,000 --> 00:01:16,000
 Our topic tonight is fascinating.

16
00:01:16,000 --> 00:01:21,000
 Belam and the donkey, AI and co-intelligence.

17
00:01:21,000 --> 00:01:26,000
 We will explore how an ancient Bible story about a talking donkey

18
00:01:26,000 --> 00:01:31,000
 might help us to understand Chagibiti, Gemini, Croc, or Deep Sea

19
00:01:31,000 --> 00:01:34,000
 and our modern world.

20
00:01:34,000 --> 00:01:40,000
 We are truly honored to have Reverend Dr. Peter Phillips with us tonight.

21
00:01:40,000 --> 00:01:44,000
 Dr. Phillips is currently at Cliff College, UK,

22
00:01:44,000 --> 00:01:47,000
 teaching and supervising PhD students

23
00:01:47,000 --> 00:01:51,000
 and building the digital theology program

24
00:01:51,000 --> 00:01:57,000
 while also serving as a Methodist minister in the Times Valley Circuit.

25
00:01:57,000 --> 00:02:03,000
 His current research focuses around the impact of digital culture on theology

26
00:02:03,000 --> 00:02:07,000
 and on temporary religious practice.

27
00:02:07,000 --> 00:02:10,000
 I met Pete many years ago.

28
00:02:10,000 --> 00:02:16,000
 I was a student in his master program in digital theology at Durham University.

29
00:02:16,000 --> 00:02:21,000
 We simply call him Pete, so I will keep calling him Pete tonight

30
00:02:21,000 --> 00:02:23,000
 to make it easier for me.

31
00:02:23,000 --> 00:02:27,000
 Learning from Pete was an eye-opening journey.

32
00:02:27,000 --> 00:02:34,000
 We study and reflect on a number of subjects like God, church, human beings,

33
00:02:34,000 --> 00:02:38,000
 evangelism, Bible, media, to name just a few.

34
00:02:38,000 --> 00:02:41,000
 What all this means in the digital age

35
00:02:41,000 --> 00:02:46,000
 has been truly an inspiration in my own learning journey.

36
00:02:46,000 --> 00:02:49,000
 So we are very happy he is here.

37
00:02:49,000 --> 00:02:56,000
 He will help us reflect on the pressing issue facing all of humanity today.

38
